# Agent Spawn Universal Rule

Before spawning:
1. Read:
   - docs/automation/LOOP_GATES.md
   - docs/automation/LOOP_CONSISTENCY_STANDARD.md
   - docs/automation/LOOP_DYNAMIC_SHARING.md
2. Define spawn intent in 1 line: role, scope, output artifact.

Spawn limits:
- Max 4 agents in parallel.
- One owner agent merges all outputs.

Each spawned agent must return:
- artifact_path
- evidence (tests/checks run)
- continuity risks
- next_steps (1-3)

After all agents finish:
1. Run continuity checks:
   - .\scripts\automation\run_loop_continuity_tests.ps1
2. If polished output exists, send to hub and index it.
3. Write shared state via dedupe-safe writer:
   - .\scripts\automation\write_loop_shared_state.ps1 ...

Guardrails:
- Non-master loops do not implement UI changes.
- Heavy changes require approval gate.
- No destructive deletes outside cleanup allowlist (see docs/agents/CLEANUP_DATA_DELETION_PROMPT.md).
